The paper deals with algebraic independence testing, which is a fundamental problem in computational complexity theory and algebraic geometry. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.AG (Algebraic Geometry). The paper also uses geometric techniques and algorithms, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation). Finally, the paper introduces a new problem called approximate polynomials satisfiability (APS) and shows that it is NP-hard and can be solved in PSPACE, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
